{
  "doc_id": "5625",
  "text": "Dobutamine stress echocardiography (DSE) is rapidly emerging as the noninvasive test of choice in the screening for allograft CAD [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] and in predicting outcome in heart transplant recipients [CITATION_3] . However, it is unclear whether the wall motion abnormalities induced during DSE have the same implications early after transplantation. To the best of our knowledge, DSE has not been used in patients with a new transplant (Ͻ2 years) in a serial fashion to assess the early development of CAD.",
